\mathscr{C}^1
f(x) - f(y) = \int_0^1 Df(y + t(x-y)).(x-y) dt
\begin{aligned} \| f(x) - f(y) \| &\le& &\int_0^1 \|Df(y+t(x-y)).(x-y) \| dt& \\ &\le& &\left( \int_0^1 \| Df( y + t(x-y) )\| dt \right) \| x-y \|& \le \sup_{z \in \mathbb{R}^n} \, \|Df(z) \| \; \| x-y \| \end{aligned}
\sup_{z \in \mathbb{R}^n} \, \| Df(z) \| = C
\| f(x) - f(y) \| \le C \|x - y \|
x,y
